This was my third try at a fruit coffee cake, and by far the best. Great flavor (I added 1/2 tsp vanilla to the dough), with a nice light dough, and so easy to make. The sugar topping was a little too strong for my taste, so I think next time I'd reduce it to 2 Tbsp sugar and 1/2 tsp cinnamon. This was a real hit and a is great way to use summer stone fruit.

Rating: 4
This is a wonderful coffee cake. Since nectarines were not available, I used a one pound bag of frozen peaches. I've also added some blueberries. I just defrosted the peach slices in the unopened bag. They worked perfectly well! I added 1 teaspoon of packed brown sugar to the topping. This has now been requested several times! It's quick and easy and delightful hot, warm or cold, with ice cream, or whipped cream or a sprinkle of powdered sugar.

Rating: 4
PS. If you can't find self-rising flour, make it yourself! 2 cups AP flour, 2 tsp baking powder, 1 tsp salt. I like to sift it and keep a jar on top of my AP flour to have when needed.

