Rating: 4
Here in Arkansas, the peach season is at its height. For this recipe, I used peeled peaches (both white and yellow) instead of nectarines. I also added a smidgen of ground cloves to the sugar and cinnamon. I gently pressed each slice of fruit into the sugar/spice mix, then placed the fruit on the cake batter, sugar-side-up. I sprinkled the remaider of the mixture on the cake as the recipe directs. The result was fantastic!!! I served the cake as a coffee cake for a Sunday brunch and everyone wanted the recipe.

Rating: 0
To the Cook from Cannes : one certainly CAN get self-raising flour (popularly known as "farine à gateaux")in France. I've even found it in relatively small village groceries, though it does help if one knows what to look for. Try the "Francine" brand - look for the the following text : Gateaux, Farine de ble et poudre levante incorporee (i.e. wheat flour with raising/ baking powder included). Haven't made the recipe yet, hence no forks.

