Rating: 4
Four forks only with modifications: This didn't seem like enough batter so I made 1.5x the amount. The idea of lemon zest didn't appeal to me so I used 1.5 teaspoons vanilla. For self-raising flour, I found a formula for it calling for 4 oz. of flour to 1.5 teaspoons baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt. I also added 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon to the batter. I used peaches and only needed 3 of them. It had to bake for a lot longer (1 hour; 30 minutes). The result was STELLAR.

